description: Imports a bacpac into a new database.

subscription_id.description: The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription.

parameters.description: The required parameters for importing a Bacpac into a database.

storagekey.description: The storage key to use.  If storage key type is SharedAccessKey, it must be preceded with a '?.'

api_version.description: The API version to use for the request.

storagekeytype.description: The type of the storage key to use.

databasename.description: The name of the database to import.

administratorlogin.description: The name of the SQL administrator.

serviceobjectivename.description: The name of the service objective to assign to the database.

resource_group_name.description: The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal.

edition.description: The edition for the database being created.The list of SKUs may vary by region and support offer. To determine the SKUs (including the SKU name, tier/edition, family, and capacity) that are available to your subscription in an Azure region, use the `Capabilities_ListByLocation` REST API or one of the following commands:```azurecliaz sql db list-editions -l  -o table```````powershellGet-AzSqlServerServiceObjective -Location ````

maxsizebytes.description: The maximum size for the newly imported database.

administratorloginpassword.description: The password of the SQL administrator.
